Easley, D., Hvidkjaer, S., & O'Hara, M. (2002). Is Information Risk Priced? The Journal of Finance, 57(5), 2185-2221.
https://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/abs/10.1111/1540-6261.00493


"We find that information asymmetry, as measured by the probability of information-based trading (PIN) derived from daily order flow, is a risk factor that significantly increases a firm's cost of capital."

